This paper deals with game theory and network optimization, which are both central topics in computer science. The use of coordination mechanisms to improve the Price of Anarchy is a common theme in algorithmic game theory, which suggests that cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves network optimization, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of mechanisms to improve the Price of Anarchy also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves social choice theory, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
